---
// "Why DeepCausality?" — capability rundown below the example grid.
// Two-column feature list at desktop, single column on mobile.
type Item = {
  title: string;
  body: string;
  links: { label: string; href: string }[];
};

const items: Item[] = [
  {
    title: 'Static, dynamic, adaptive, and emergent causality',
    body:
      'Model causal structure that is fixed at design time, evolves over the lifetime of a system, adapts to feedback, ' +
        'or arises from interaction. The same primitives carry across all four modalities, so the choice is a modeling decision.',
    links: [{ label: 'Concept: dynamic causality', href: '/docs/concepts/dynamic-causality/' }],
  },
  {
    title: 'Multi-shaped causality',
    body:
      'Express a single rule as a Causaloid, a flat collection of Causaloids, or a hypergraph of nested Causaloids. ' +
        'The shape follows the problem: an isolated guard, a battery of independent checks, or a deeply composed causal structure with subgraphs and shared subexpressions.',
    links: [{ label: 'Concept: Causaloid', href: '/docs/concepts/causaloid/' }],
  },
  {
    title: 'Causal discovery via CDL',
    body:
      'The Causal Discovery Language is a typestate-driven DSL that walks raw observational data through configuration, loading, feature selection, discovery, and analysis. Each stage is enforced by the type system.',
    links: [{ label: 'Concept: CDL', href: '/docs/concepts/cdl/' }],
  },
  {
    title: 'Causal State Machines (CSM)',
    body:
      'Wire Causaloids to actions and let the framework drive the transitions. The CSM pattern is the right fit for sensor monitoring, alerting, and control loops where a state change has to follow a causal verdict.',
    links: [
      { label: 'Concept: CSM', href: '/docs/concepts/csm/' },
      { label: 'Example: sensor monitoring with CSM', href: '/examples/sensor-monitoring-csm/' },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Static and dynamic context',
    body:
      'Causaloids run inside a Context: a hypergraph of the data, time, and space they depend on. A static context is defined up front; a dynamic context grows, shrinks, or rewires at runtime as new information arrives.',
    links: [{ label: 'Concept: Context', href: '/docs/concepts/context/' }],
  },
  {
    title: 'Multimodal reasoning',
    body:
      'A single graph can reason deterministically, probabilistically, counterfactually, or in any combination. The PropagatingEffect type carries the modality through the graph.',
    links: [
      { label: 'Concept: Effect Propagation Process', href: '/docs/concepts/effect-propagation-process/' },
      { label: 'Example: Pearl counterfactual', href: '/examples/pearl-counterfactual/' },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Markovian and non-Markovian modeling',
    body:
      'PropagatingEffect carries the immediate signal; PropagatingProcess carries the trajectory of effects over time. Together they let a model reason about systems whose next state depends on the current state, on full history, or on anything in between.',
    links: [{ label: 'Concept: Effect Propagation Process', href: '/docs/concepts/effect-propagation-process/' }],
  },
  {
    title: 'First-class uncertainty',
    body:
      'Uncertain<T> wraps a value whose distribution is known but whose exact value is not. MaybeUncertain<T> goes further and represents probabilistic presence: a value that may or may not be there. Both compose with the rest of the framework without breaking type safety.',
    links: [{ label: 'Concept: uncertainty', href: '/docs/concepts/uncertainty/' }],
  },
  {
    title: 'Uniform mathematical composition',
    body:
      'Tensors, multivectors, manifolds, and sparse matrices expose the same Functor/Monad/CoMonad surface through HAFT and the algebraic trait hierarchy.',
    links: [
      { label: 'Concept: uniform mathematical foundation', href: '/docs/concepts/uniform-math/' },
      { label: 'Concept: Higher-Kinded Types', href: '/docs/concepts/hkt/' },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Programmable safety with the Effect Ethos',
    body:
      'The Effect Ethos is a programmable policy layer that verifies operational rules over the effects a graph produces. It lets safety-critical and regulated systems encode "what is allowed to happen" alongside "what does happen," checked deterministically at runtime.',
    links: [{ label: 'Concept: Effect Ethos', href: '/docs/concepts/effect-ethos/' }],
  },
];
---
<section class="why">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <h2>What DeepCausality can do for you</h2>

    <dl class="features">
      {items.map((item) => (
        <div class="feature">
          <dt>{item.title}</dt>
          <dd>
            <p>{item.body}</p>
            <p class="links">
              {item.links.map((link, i) => (
                <>
                  {i > 0 && <span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>}
                  <a href={link.href}>{link.label} &rarr;</a>
                </>
              ))}
            </p>
          </dd>
        </div>
      ))}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .why {
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
  }
  .why-inner {
    max-width: var(--w-page);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-4);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  .why-inner > h2 { text-align: center; }
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .why { padding: var(--space-9) 0; }
    .why-inner { padding: 0 var(--space-5); }
  }
  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--t-eyebrow); letter-spacing: var(--ls-eyebrow);
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-2);
  }
  h2 { margin: 0; }
  .lede {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3) 0;
    color: var(--fg-1);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .features {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6) var(--space-7);
  }
  .features > * { min-width: 0; }
  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .features { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }

  .feature {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-1);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  .feature dt {
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--fg-0);
    font-size: var(--t-h4);
    line-height: var(--lh-h4);
  }
  .feature dd { margin: 0; }
  .feature dd p { margin: 0 0 var(--space-2) 0; color: var(--fg-1); }
  .feature dd p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--t-body-sm);
  }
  .links a {
    color: var(--accent);
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .links .sep { color: var(--fg-2); }
</style>
